we can have method body in interface. But we need to make it default method.method body allowed whe it id default method
java.

interface Destination {  
void travel();  
default void msg(){System.out.println("default method");}  
}  
class Bus implements Destination{  
public void drive(){System.out.println("driving");}  
}  
class Way{  
public static void main(String args[]){  
Destination d=new Bus();  
d.drive();  
d.travel();  
}}  




Interface fields are public, static and final by default, and the methods are public and abstract.
int a=10; == public static final int a=10
and methods are
public abtract void travel(){

